  Requirements Before Installing:

A Nexus Premium account is required.
All Fallout 4 DLC is required, except for the Hi Res DLC.
100 gigs of free space.
A clean Fallout 4 installation.

Installation Instructions:

Download the latest version of Wabbajack from Github or the #builds channel on the Wabbajack Discord server.
Save/move Wabbajack.exe into a new folder called Wabbajack. Keep this folder at the root of a drive (example: D:\Wabbajack).
Download the latest BananaSplit.modlist_v2 file from the release channel on the Wabbajack Discord.
Save the modlist file to the same folder in which you downloaded Wabbajack.
Create a new folder at the root of your drive (example: D:\Banana Split).
Launch Wabbajack.exe.
Click "Install a Modlist"
Navigate to the Wabbajack folder, and select the BananaSplit.modlist_v2 file.
In the "Installation Location" selection, navigate to the new Banana Split folder you just created.
The "Download Location" section should autocomplete.
Click "Begin"
This length of this process varies depending on your system specs. It will most likely take several hours.
Do not close Wabbajack before it prompts you to do so. A message will appear in the bottom left pane when installation is complete.

Post Installation Instructions:

Navigate to the folder in which you installed the Banana Split modlist.
Open the "Game Folder Files" folder.
Select all of the loose files, as well as the "ENB Series" folder.
Right click and select "Copy"
Navigate to your FO4 directory (steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4).
Right click in a blank area and select "Paste"
Navigate back to your modlist installation folder.
Launch the ModOrganizer.exe file.
In the dropdown list of executables, click <Edit...>
In the left pane, click "FO4 QuickAutoClean"
Update the "Binary" and Start In" paths to make sure they align with your setup. This tool is included with your modlist installation, in the Tools folder.
When finished, select OK to close the window.
In the dropdown list of executables, navigate to "FO4 QuickAutoClean"
Select "Run"
A window will pop up with all of the mods in the load order. All of the checkboxes will be unticked.
Only select ONE file at a time.
Note: If you have multiple FO4 modlist installations, make a backup of your vanilla ESMs before cleaning, then add the cleaned ESMs to a new folder called "Cleaned ESMs" and install it as a mod, then return the vanilla ESMs to the Fallout 4 directory.

DO NOT CLEAN FALLOUT4.ESM

The files you need to clean are the following:
DLCRobot.esm
DLCWorkshop1.esm
DLCWorkshop2.esm
DLCWorkshop3.esm
DLCCoast.esm
DLCNukaWorld.esm

When cleaning is complete, head over to http://enbdev.com/mod_fallout4_v0393.htm.
Download the 0.393 archive.
Extract the enbseries archive.
Open the Wrapper Version.
Copy d3d11.dll and d3dcompiler_46e.dll.
Paste them into your Fallout 4 directory.
Copy all loose files in Game Folder Files, as well as the enbseries folder.
Paste them into your FO4 directory.

Congrats, that's it! Now you can play the Banana Split modlist. Make sure to always launch the game with the F4SE option via Mod Organizer 2.
However, there are still a few steps to take to make the game behave properly.

Post-Installation Instructions:

ImmersiveHUD MCM:
You can set the default options to whatever you like.

VAFS Redux MCM:
Change the "Focus" hotkey to Q, and the "Critical" hotkey to Z.
Note that if you do set VAFS to Q, you will have to open the game settings and unbind VATS, or move it to a key other than Q.

WheelMenu MCM:
Change the "Toggle Key" to whatever you like. I use Mouse4.

Workshop Framework MCM:
Select the "Options Tab.
Change "Allow Settlements to Leave" to Off (if you want).

Workshop Plus MCM:
Hotkeys:
Undo: Ctrl+Z
Toggle Flight: B
Toggle Speed Buff: N

